Array is a collection of similar type of elements which has contiguous memory location
elements of a similar data type. you cannot declare a single array that holds both strings AND integers

Advantages
Code Optimization: It makes the code optimized, we can retrieve or sort the data efficiently
Random access: We can get any data located at an index position

store only the fixed size of elements in the array

declare, instantiate and initialize the java array together  ex- int a[]={33,3,4,5}

return an array from the method in Java - return new int[]{10,30,50,90,60}

ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException - length of the array in negative, equal to the array size or greater than the array size while traversing the array

